The JEWEL Tower, Westminster London that reveals the interior rooms. The JEWEL Tower is a surviving part of the original Palace of Westminster. It was built to house the monarchs treasure and personal possessions until 1512. The ground floor has a beautiful carved stone ceiling and now houses the cafe, shop and entrance. The rest of the tower is a small and very interesting.
